enhanced.TORES: The surface described by the circumference of a circle revolving about a straight line in its own plane.
enhanced.TORN: To rend (a solid material) by holding or restraining in two places and pulling apart, whether intentionally or not; to destroy or separate.
enhanced.TOSS: A throw, a lob, of a ball etc., with an initial upward direction, particularly with a lack of care.
enhanced.TOSSER: One who tosses or throws something.
enhanced.TRES: A three-course stringed instrument similar to a guitar; the Cuban variant has six strings, and the Puerto Rican has nine.
enhanced.TRESS: A braid, knot, or curl, of hair; a ringlet.
